defaultpublic bodies. An increasing number of people are receiving public services through multi-agency arrangements. 
defaultThe administration of services which have been the responsibility of central government departments, such as welfare benefits and health care are also now being devolved to local authorities. This devolved system includes new bodies to support 
defaultlocal accountability and 
defaultcomplaints handling, such as Healthwatch
default. 
default 
defaultThe public should not have to make complex determinations about who is 
defaultaccountable for 
defaultdelivering their service
default, and therefore liable for redress,
default 
defaultand which Ombudsman can help them when those services
default fail.
default The proposals we make below have the aim of providing users of all public services in England with a seamless
